context: The patient had tympanoplasty surgery for a traumatic perforation of the right ear about six weeks ago.
The left eardrum (not the surgical ear) has a definite infection with a reddened bulging drum but no perforation or granulation tissue.

Since he recently had a course of Omnicef we chose to put him on Augmentin (I checked and we did not have samples), so I phoned in a two-week course of Augmentin 400 mg chewable twice daily with food at Walgreens.
